<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-1020] Incorrect XML escape in &lt;system-out&gt; and &lt;system-err&gt; content of junit xml report</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1020</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JUnit XML report contains invalid XML characters in &amp;lt;system-out&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;system-err&amp;gt; content. The illegal characters handling defined in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-456&quot; title=&quot;Surefire doubly XML-escapes non-visible control characters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-456&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-456&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; doesn&apos;t work since version 2.15. The problem is that &lt;b&gt;EncodingOutputStream&lt;/b&gt; in &lt;b&gt;StatelessXmlReporter&lt;/b&gt; does not convert the illegal XML characters to their string representation (e.g. 0 -&amp;gt; &quot;0&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please find attached a possible fix for this issue as well as extended test case that includes illegal XML characters in system-out and system-err content.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
